{"file_name":"BX6CS4BF.pdf","response_content":"{\"organism_trends\": [\n{\n\"Hauptgruppe_RoteListen\": {\n\"content\": \"Pilze_Flechten\",\n\"evidence_anchor\": \"As phomonoesters are the major form of soil organic P (McLaren et al., 2020), we expected microbes to rely mainly on non-specific acid (ACP) and alkaline (ALP) phosphomonoesterases for organic P mineralization.\"\n},\n\"Untergruppe_RoteListen\": {\n\"content\": \"Flechten\",\n\"evidence_anchor\": \"As phomonoesters are the major form of soil organic P (McLaren et al., 2020), we expected microbes to rely mainly on non-specific acid (ACP) and alkaline (ALP) phosphomonoesterases for organic P mineralization.\"\n},\n\"Lebensraum\": {\n\"content\": \"Wald\",\n\"evidence_anchor\": \"In long-term agricultural trials, fertilization and management treatments are known to shift the taxon abundances and composition of microbial communities harboring _ALP_ genes, whereby pH, organic carbon (C), and total N along with soil P are the dominant influencing factors (Chen et al., 2017; Chhabra et al., 2013; Fraser et al., 2015a; Hu et al., 2018; Ragot et al., 2016; Tan et al., 2013).\"\n},\n\"Antwortvariable\": {\n\"content\": \"Abundanz\",\n\"evidence_anchor\": \"For bacteria, a quarter of the observed orders were abundant in the studies of Bergkemper et al. (2016b) and Meller (2019) that investigated mineral horizons from the same sites.\"\n},\n\"Trend\": {\n\"content\": \"negative\",\n\"evidence_anchor\": \"increasing N deposition might thus pose greater impacts on microbial communities in low-P compared to high-P sites, by further increasing the already high competition for P.\"\n}\n},\n{\n\"Hauptgruppe_RoteListen\": {\n\"content\": \"Pflanzen\",\n\"evidence_anchor\": \"Lang et al. (2017) hypothesized that the nutrition strategy and corresponding tightness of P cycling depend on the P status of the soil.\"\n},\n\"Untergruppe_RoteListen\": null,\n\"Lebensraum\": {\n\"content\": \"Wald\",\n\"evidence_anchor\": \"Understa