{"file_name":"VQT78VA5.pdf","response_content":"{\"organism_trends\": [\n{\n\"Hauptgruppe_RoteListen\": {\n\"content\": \"Wirbellose\",\n\"evidence_anchor\": \"Due to stemflow water running down beech trees _(Fagus sylvatica_ L.) pollutants (protons, heavy metals) accumulate in the vicinity of the trunk in beech forests in central Europe. This study investigates density, biomass, species composition and depth distribution of major soil macrofauna groups (Diplopoda, Isopoda, Lumbricidae, Chilopoda) near beech trees and distant to trees in a beechwood on limestone in northern Germany each season for 1 year.\"\n},\n\"Untergruppe_RoteListen\": {\n\"content\": \"Arthropoden\",\n\"evidence_anchor\": \"The soil macrofauna (Diplopoda, Isopoda, Lumbricidae and Chilopoda) near tree trunks in a beechwood on limestone:\"\n},\n\"Lebensraum\": {\n\"content\": \"Wald\",\n\"evidence_anchor\": \"The soil macrofauna (Diplopoda, Isopoda, Lumbricidae and Chilopoda) near tree trunks in a beechwood on limestone:\"\n},\n\"Antwortvariable\": {\n\"content\": \"Abundanz\",\n\"evidence_anchor\": \"Generally, the density of soil-inhabiting (endogeic) species was lower in the tree vicinity, whereas the density of species inhabiting predominantly the litter layer (epigeic species) was similar to or higher than that distant to trees.\"\n},\n\"Trend\": {\n\"content\": \"negative\",\n\"evidence_anchor\": \"Generally, the density of soil-inhabiting (endogeic) species was lower in the tree vicinity, whereas the density of species inhabiting predominantly the litter layer (epigeic species) was similar to or higher than that distant to trees.\"\n}\n},\n{\n\"Hauptgruppe_RoteListen\": {\n\"content\": \"Wirbellose\",\n\"evidence_anchor\": \"Generally, the density of soil-inhabiting (endogeic) species was lower in the tree vicinity, whereas the density of species inhabiting predominantly the litter layer (epigeic species) was similar to or higher than that distant to trees.\"\n},\n\"Untergruppe_RoteListen\